commText: Welcome back for the run-chase! Narine has a new opening partner in Gurbaz tonight. The former's form with the bat has dipped off late but if he can get going, he will be difficult to stop. Bhuvneshwar to start off with the new ball. A slip in place. Here we go...
SRH innings progression Overs 1-7: 50/4 (RR: 7.14) Overs 8-12: 60/1 (RR: 12.00) Overs 13-19.3: 49/5 (RR: 6.53)
20 wickets by Varun Chakaravarthy this season is the joint-most for him in an IPL edition. Last year he took 20 wickets as well.

Highest 10th wicket partnership in the IPL 55* - Shikhar Dhawan & M Rathee (PBKS) vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2023 33 - Pat Cummins & V Viyaskanth (SRH) vs KKR, Ahmedabad, 2024* 31* - Tom Curran & Ankit Rajpoot (RR) vs KKR, Dubai, 2020 31 - Andre Russell & CV Varun (KKR) vs DC, Delhi, 2023

Best bowling figures for KKR in the playoffs 4/21 - Sunil Narine vs RCB, Sharjah, 2021 3/13 - Umesh Yadav vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2014 3/20 - Nathan Coulter-Nile vs SRH, Bengaluru, 2017 3/34 - Mitchell Starc vs SRH, Ahmedabad, 2024* 3/35 - Kuldeep Yadav vs SRH, Delhi, 2016

Mitch Starc: I have been fortunate enough to play on some big occasions, nice to get our team off to a good start, we know how SRH matched us in terms of attacking with the bat in the powerplay. Their (Head and Abhishek) partnership has been the key for them and to get both of them out cheaply, it's really pleasing. The wicket's got a bit skidier and there is some swing as well, I feel the wicket will get better with dew and the powerplay will be really key for us.

21:17 Local Time, 15:47 GMT, 21:17 IST: SRH have only managed to post a middling total in an important match. Perhaps, the decision to win the toss and bat first backfired on them. Starc was in his elements from the get-go and knocked over Head for a duck. Abhishek also departed cheaply as he holed out to covers to Arora. The Australian should have got his second wicket as well when Tripathi was trapped in front but KKR didn't review. But, Starc was relentless and picked up two more wickets in two balls to push SRH into a tangle at 39/4. It was in the 9th over that SRH got some momentum with Narine leaking 18 runs. But soon after that, Chakravarthy struck in his first over to send the dangerous Klaasen packing. Tripathi continued to play well from the other end and scored a fine fifty but a needless run-out sent him packing. The Impact sub flopped and the wickets continued to tumble. Chakravarthy once again bowled a top spell to choke SRH. Cummins played a good cameo but 159 is below-par on a surface which is pretty good for batting. The odd-ball is sticking and there's some extra bounce too but KKR have the firepower to chase this down...

Russell to Cummins, out Caught by Gurbaz!! Cummins falls after playing a cameo! Fuller length ball angling in, Cummins clears his front leg and swings at it but only manages to edge it to his right. It's high in the night sky. Gurbaz calls for it and takes a fine running catch. SRH are bowled out for 159. Cummins c Gurbaz b Russell 30(24) [4s-2 6s-2]
Russell to Cummins, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Russell to Cummins, no run, a fine yorker tailing in on middle and leg, Cummins digs it out to the left of Russell

Russell to V Viyaskanth, 3 runs, lazy work in the field! A short of length ball well outside off, Viyaskanth upper cuts it over backward point and Cummins calls his partner through for the second. Rana takes it casual and underarms the throw to the keeper which allows Cummins to take the third run
Andre Russell [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Starc to Cummins, FOUR, smart from Cummins! Fuller length ball outside off, Cummins knows where the gap is. He opens his bat-face and carves it past the left side of backward point to find the fence

Starc to Cummins, SIX, straight up but it not only clears short third but also the fence! A length ball shaping in, Cummins swings hard across the line but gets a big top-edge. The fielder tracks back but he can only see it flying over the fence

Starc to Cummins, no run, almost chopped on! Full ball tailing back in nicely, Cummins pushes at it with minimal foot movement and gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball then lobs over the stumps
Starc to V Viyaskanth, 1 run, Starc tucks Viyaskanth with a back of a length bal that shoots off the deck. He hops and somehow manages to run it down to third man
Starc to Cummins, 1 run, fuller length ball angling in on off, Cummins hits it off the inner half towards wide long-on

Starc to Cummins, no run, hat-trick ball but Starc doesn't get it. Was a yorker length ball that tailed in from outside off, Cummins looks to carve it through point but gets an inside edge onto the pads
Mitchell Starc [3.0-0-22-3] is back into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Cummins, 1 run, full ball drifting in from outside off, driven against the angle to sweeper cover. Another top spell from Chakaravarthy
Chakaravarthy to V Viyaskanth, 1 run, quick and full this time, drifting in, Viyaskanth seems to have got an inside edge onto his pads and the ball deflects towards short fine
Chakaravarthy to Cummins, 1 run, floated delivery on off, Cummins drags his slog sweep to deep backward square leg. Shouts of catch it but it falls short of the man there
Chakaravarthy to V Viyaskanth, 1 run, tossed up outside off, Viyaskanth strokes it to long-off to get off strike
A slip in place for No. 11
Chakaravarthy to Cummins, 1 run, quicker through the air on off, Cummins slogs it off the inner half to deep squar leg

Chakaravarthy to Cummins, SIX, that's an audacious stroke! Cummins premeditates and switches his stance. Employs the reverse hit to perfection to the back of a length ball on off and plays it over the third man fence
Harshit Rana to Cummins, 1 run, an off-cutter on a good length outside off, dabbed to short third to retain strike

Harshit Rana to Cummins, FOUR, nicely played! A back of a length ball outside off, Cummins stays leg-side of the ball and opens the face of his bat to guide the cut nicely past the left side of the diving backward point fielder. Gets the desired result
Harshit Rana to V Viyaskanth, 1 run, fuller length ball outside off, Viyaskanth pushes it off the outer half of his bat to the right of third man
Harshit Rana to Cummins, 1 run, another off-pace ball outside off, Cummins dabs it towards short third and calls his partner through for a brisk single
40 runs is the joint-most Sunil Narine conceded in an inning this IPL. He conceded 1/40 against RCB at Bengaluru earlier this season.
Harshit Rana to Cummins, no run, another off-cutter on a length that grips, Cummins is early into his slog and misses again and the ball flies over the stumps

Harshit Rana to Cummins, no run, A slower length ball angling in, Cummins looks to slog across the line but only meets thin air. That wasn't far from the leg-stump and Harshit Rana has his hands on his head
Vijayakanth Viyaskanth, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Chakaravarthy to Bhuvneshwar, out Lbw!! Bhuvneshwar has been trapped in front but he takes the review! Looked adjacent to the naked eye. The only thing that can save him if it slides down leg. Was a length ball on off that spun in sharply, Bhuvneshwar played down the wrong line and was pinged on the pads. Time for the replays. There's a flat line on Ultra Edge. Over to ball-tracking and hitting is umpire's call. Would have clipped the top of leg-stump. SRH in danger of being bowled out. Bhuvneshwar lbw b Chakaravarthy 0(4)
Chakaravarthy to Bhuvneshwar, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!
Chakaravarthy to Bhuvneshwar, no run, an appeal for an lbw cut short! Tossed up outside off, Bhuvneshwar plays around it and is struck on the pads. The impact was probably outside off
Chakaravarthy to Cummins, 1 run, just short of long-on! Cummins leans ahead and goes for an expansive stroke but gets it off the toe-end. The fielder runs in but it reaches him on the bounce
Chakaravarthy to Cummins, no run, defensive bowling this time as Chakaravarthy fires it on a back of a length well outside off, Cummins lets it go
Chakaravarthy to Cummins, no run, on a back of a length around off, Cummins steers it straight to the slip fielder
Chakaravarthy to Cummins, no run, oh, almost sneaked through! An in-drifter on a fuller length around off, Cummins goes for a slog sweep but gets an inside edge onto the pads
Varun Chakaravarthy [2.0-0-14-1] is back into the attack

Over Summary (11-15) -> Chakravathy strikes in his first over, gets the big fish - Klaasen -> Samad opens his account with a maximum against Sunil Narine -> An excellent effort by Russell results in Tripathi's run-out -> Impact player Sanvir walks back without troubling the scorers -> Samad is the 8th wicket down, departs after playing a cameo
Harshit Rana to Bhuvneshwar, no run, back of a length ball in the off-stump channel, Bhuvneshwar hops and keeps it out
Harshit Rana to Bhuvneshwar, no run, pacy short of length ball outside off and there's room on offer, Bhuvneshwar slashes and misses
Bhuvneshwar Kumar, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshit Rana to Abdul Samad, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! Another one bites the dust! SRH are falling like a pack of cards! A slower length ball outside off, Abdul Samad uses his feet and makes a bit of room but he is not to the pitch of it. Still goes through with his swing and mistimes it towards long-off. Shreyas Iyer near the ropes is cool as a cucumber and pouches it safely. Abdul Samad c Shreyas Iyer b Harshit Rana 16(12) [6s-2]
Harshit Rana to Abdul Samad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Harshit Rana to Cummins, 1 run, Cummins makes room and Harshit Rana follows him with a back of a length ball. He hops and works it through wide mid-on
Harshit Rana to Abdul Samad, 1 run, slower good length ball outside off, Abdul Samad punches it to sweeper cover
Harshit Rana to Abdul Samad, no run, skiddy back of a length ball outside off, Abdul Samad looks to force it through covers but only meets thin air
Harshit Rana [2.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Narine to Cummins, no run, well bowled! Quick and flat just outside off, turns the other way this time, Cummins pokes at it and gets beaten
Narine to Cummins, no run, a bit quicker through the air, Cummins keeps it out watchfully
Narine to Cummins, 2 runs, tossed up on off, Cummins works it through square leg and rushes back for the second run
Pat Cummins, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Narine to Sanvir Singh, out Bowled!! Two wickets in two balls and the momentum has swung once more! 92.6kph length ball on middle, pitches and turns and grips, Sanvir Singh leans ahead tentatively to counter it but leaves a bat-pad gap. The ball deflects off his pads and crashes into the stumps. Sanvir Singh b Narine 0(1)
Narine to Sanvir Singh, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Sanvir Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Sanvir Singh comes in as the Impact sub for Abhishek Sharma for SRH

Narine to Abdul Samad, out Tripathi Run Out!! Brilliant stuff from Russell and KKR get the well-set Tripathi! On a back of a length outside off, Abdul Samad chops it to the left of Russell at backward point who dives to make a great stop. Abdul Samad continues to run while Tripathi is ball-watching. Abdul Samad has crossed Tripathi and the latter is stranded in the middle. The throw comes in and Gurbaz does the rest. An unnecessary dismissal this but KKR won't mind one bit. Tripathi run out (Russell/Gurbaz) 55(35) [4s-7 6s-1]
Narine to Abdul Samad, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Narine to Abdul Samad, SIX, what a shot! Narine continues to leak runs. Abdul Samad uses his feet, converts this one into a slot ball and smashes it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum. He hit that so well
Timeout! Wickets column, the biggest concern for SRH. KKR are not complaining though. They would be keen to keep SRH under 170 which appears to be a below par total on this wicket...

Chakaravarthy to Abdul Samad, 1 run, floated full on the stumps, Samad slogs to the right of Starc at long-on. Shouts of "Catch it", but Starc decided to save the boundary and sat back to cover the line of the ball
Chakaravarthy to Tripathi, 1 run, full outside off, Tripathi advances and forces the drive to the right of long-off
Chakaravarthy to Tripathi, no run, short outside off, punched away to the left of backward point
Chakaravarthy to Abdul Samad, 1 run, flat and just outside off, clipped away into the mid-wicket pocket
Chakaravarthy to Abdul Samad, no run, comes down the track and slices the drive to the right of short third. Thinks of a quick single, but sent back!
Stat: Klaasen got out to spin 5 times in his last 7 matches. He was out to spin only once in the first six matches of the season.
Chakaravarthy to Tripathi, 1 run, full and fast just outside off, flicked away to the right of deep mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Tripathi, wide, spins down leg from a length, Tripathi doesn't bother with it

Narine to Abdul Samad, 1 run, quicker and just outside off, pushed away to the right of mid-wicket

Narine to Abdul Samad, SIX, no sighters needed says Abdul Samad. With a solid base at the crease, watches this full delivery dip in his arc and he's marmalized it into the cow corner orbit for a maximum
Narine to Tripathi, 1 run, flat on off, Tripathi knocks it to the right of the bowler and a slight fumble allows the batters to sneak a quick single

Abdul Samad, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, out Caught by Rinku Singh!! KKR get the big fish. Chakaravarthy goes fast and full just outside off, lured Klaasen into a slog but also forced him to hit to the longer part of the ground. Klaasen's slog didn't find the desired connection and Rinku makes no mistake at deep mid-wicket. Runs across to his right and completes the catch with ease. Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Chakaravarthy to Tripathi, 1 run, floated up just outside off, clipped away to mid-wicket for a quick single

Chakaravarthy to Tripathi, FOUR, goes for the reverse sweep and hits the gap to perfection. Rahul Tripathi brings up his 12th IPL fifty and one that he'll remember for a long time given the situation of the game. He stayed low and got enough contact to beat Russell at backward point to his right
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, 1 run, quicker and wider of off, Klaasen slaps it off the back foot to deep cover
Chakaravarthy to Tripathi, 1 run, short outside off, Tripathi opens the bat face and punches to the left of sweeper cover
Chakaravarthy to Tripathi, no run, excellent follow-up delivery from Varun Chakaravarthy. A yorker length delivery on the stumps and Tripathi can only squeeze it back to the bowler
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, no ball, 1 run, gee! It's a front foot no ball from a spinner. A full delivery on the stumps and Klaasen has flicked it along the ground to deep mid-wicket

Over Summary (6-10) -> 50 up for Sunrisers Hyderabad in the 7th over -> Counterattack by Klaasen and Tripathi -> Narine proving to be expensive, concedes 18 runs in an over -> 50-run stand up between Tripathi and Klaasen -> Match getting interesting, Sunrisers back in it
Russell to Klaasen, 1 run, short of length outside off, punched down to the left of long-on
Russell to Tripathi, 1 run, I0$ short outside off, Tripathi seeks to pull and the top-edge falls in no-man's land around the mid-wicket area
Russell to Tripathi, FOUR, 50 partnership comes up between the duo. Bumper outside off, Tripathi leaps up on his toes and helps it over the keeper with a well-timed ramp
Russell to Klaasen, 1 run, cut away to deep backward point
Russell to Klaasen, FOUR, short and wide of off, Klaasen stands tall and flays it over backward point for a near-maximum. SRH gaining some much-needed momentum...
Russell to Tripathi, 1 run, slower length delivery on off, punched down to long-on
Rahul Tripathi vs Russell in IPL (before today) Inns: 4 Runs: 38 Balls: 23 Dismissals: 4 Avg: 9.5 SR: 165.2

Narine to Klaasen, FOUR, beats Russell once again - this time along the ground. SRH have scored 18 runs off a Sunil Narine over. Not too many teams did that to Narine this season, remember. Once again it was the pace and width on the delivery that allowed Klaasen to smack it along the ground to beat long-off to his left

Narine to Klaasen, SIX, shouts of "catch it" and all the SRH fans had their hearts in their mouth for a moment. It was quick and short from Narine, Klaasen stands on the back foot and lofts it high into the night sky and manages to clear the fielder at long-off quite comfortably...
Narine to Klaasen, 2 runs, allows the ball to spin and crunches it to the left of Russell at long-on. Early call for a second and they complete it without any fuss
Narine to Tripathi, 1 run, full and wide of off, Tripathi drags the sweep off the thick inside half to the right of deep square
Narine to Tripathi, FOUR, goes full and fast on the stumps, Tripathi gets really low and paddle-scoops it really fine over the keeper. The quick outfield takes care of the rest...
Narine to Klaasen, 1 run, quicker on the stumps, Klaasen goes on the back foot and punches it to the right of long-on

Time-out! Not the ideal start for SRH after winning the toss, and a lot will rely on this partnership if they are to post a competitive total. As for KKR, they will look to squeeze through the middle overs with spin and won't make it any easy for the team in Orange.
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, 1 run, I0$ length outside off, punched down the ground towards long-on
This is the third-lowest powerplay score for SRH this season after 37/2 vs RR at Hyderabad and 40/3 vs PBKS at Mullanpur.
Harshit Rana to Tripathi, 1 run, I0$ length outside off, stabbed away to deep cover
Harshit Rana to Tripathi, SIX, connects with the ramp this time around. Another bumper and Tripathi's both feet went up in the air as he helped it over the keeper for a maximum
Harshit Rana to Tripathi, wide, I0$ lifter outside off, Tripathi looks for a ramp but that was well wide of his reach. Too high...
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, 1 run, I0$ back of a length outside off, punched away to the left of deep backward point
Harshit Rana to Tripathi, 1 run, I0$ short of length outside off, Tripathi opens the bat face and steers it fine of third man
This is the second time SRH has lost four wickets inside the powerplay this season. They were 62/4 after 6 overs against RCB at Hyderabad.
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, 1 run, I0$ short and wide of off, Klaasen drags the pull to the right of long-on
Narine to Klaasen, 1 run, shortish on off-stump, Klaasen punches it to the right of the bowler and Narine palms it away to the left of long-on
Narine to Tripathi, 1 run, fired in on leg stump, flicked away into the mid-wicket pocket
Narine to Klaasen, 1 run, flat outside off, punched down the ground to long-off

Over summary (1-5) -> Starc strikes in the first over, Head is clean bowled -> Abhishek Sharma is gone early too, Arora gets his wicket -> Tripathi survives an lbw scare, KKR don't review it -> Mitchell Starc at his best, SRH reduced to 39/4 in 5 overs!
Harshit Rana, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Starc to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Bowled!! Mitch Starc is on fire. He's got three and is on a hat-trick as well. Bowls a pacy length delivery around off and Shahbaz's lack of feet on the poke meant he got a thick inside edge that flew back to dislodge the middle stump. A nothing shot and SRH are 4 down inside 5 overs. Shahbaz Ahmed b Starc 0(1)
Starc to Shahbaz Ahmed, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Shahbaz Ahmed, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Starc to Nitish Reddy, out Caught by Gurbaz!! Too easy. Mitchell Starc has played enough cricket to understand what and when to bowl inside the powerplay. After trying out a few length balls, he goes for the bumper outside off. Cramps Nitish Reddy up for room and induces a thick top-edge that's been safely snaffled by the keeper to his left. Nitish Reddy c Gurbaz b Starc 9(10) [4s-1]
Starc to Nitish Reddy, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Vaibhav Arora to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, 129ks good length on the stumps, flicked away to the right of mid-wicket and Nitish Reddy calls his partner through for a quick single. A direct hit at the bowling end would have been interesting, but not to be

Stat: For first time in this season, both SRH openers got out in the single-digit score
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, no run, I0$ back of a length delivery on the stumps, Tripathi jumps across and blocks
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, 2 runs, advances and chips the length delivery over mid-off, more off the inside half but good enough to fetch him a couple of runs
Starc to Nitish Reddy, no run, short of length outside off, Nitish Reddy pushes it to the left of backward point
Starc to Nitish Reddy, no run, short and wide of off, Nitish Reddy doesn't bother with it

Starc to Tripathi, 1 run, oh dear! Looks like it is pad first. Starc wasn't sure and Shreyas Iyer wasn't convinced either. It would have been out lbw had they reviewed. Full inswinging toe-crusher from Starc, Tripathi was late in getting his bat down and the ball hit the boot before catching the inside edge. Starc went up in appeal, but didn't get a great deal of support frim the close-in fielders...
KKR think they have got Tripathi out lbw. Will they go for the review? Oops! Nope. Shreyas Iyer has a chat with the bowler and decides against it....

Starc to Tripathi, FOUR, Tripathi is not gonna let the wickets column impact his shot-selection. He shuffles early, gets low and scoops a length delivery with decent timing past the leaping keeper to his left

Tried to force the drive through the off-side and ends up slicing it off the top half towards cover where Dre Russ times his jump to absolute perfection to claim a well-judged catch above his head.
